249
00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:44.621
Okay. I'm gonna
need your weapons.

250
00:12:44.731 --> 00:12:47.428
It was a good shoot. Captain.
He ran. he was taking cover.

251
00:12:47.567 --> 00:12:49.001
Stop talking. Detective.

252
00:12:49.302 --> 00:12:50.600
Say nothing to anyone.

253
00:12:50.703 --> 00:12:52.865
Wait for your delegate. I'll
take your guns over here.

254
00:12:53.673 --> 00:12:57.166
Get his name to Real Time.
see if they have anything on him.

255
00:12:57.277 --> 00:12:59.769
Confiscate phones. Somebody
could've gotten this on video.

256
00:12:59.879 --> 00:13:00.956
This crowd isn't gonna help us.

257
00:13:00.980 --> 00:13:02.539
Well. convince them otherwise.

258
00:13:02.849 --> 00:13:04.426
Where the hell's that
bus? He's slipping away.

259
00:13:04.450 --> 00:13:06.170
Okay. the bus is on
its way. They're coming.

260
00:13:06.252 --> 00:13:07.584
Listen. I'm gonna stay with him.

261
00:13:07.687 --> 00:13:08.950
You go. go search the building.

262
00:13:09.055 --> 00:13:10.295
Shouldn't I wait for a warrant?

263
00:13:10.356 --> 00:13:12.018
Yeah. I'm gonna
call one in. okay.

264
00:13:12.191 --> 00:13:13.887
In the meantime. just
get creative. okay?

265
00:13:13.993 --> 00:13:16.639
He stole their money. He stole
their credit cards and their jewelry.

266
00:13:16.663 --> 00:13:18.256
We need to tie him
to those rapes ASAP.

267
00:13:18.364 --> 00:13:19.662
All right.

268
00:13:25.305 --> 00:13:26.515
Where does Terrence
keep his stuff?

269
00:13:26.539 --> 00:13:28.250
Hey. don't you need a
warrant? It'll be here any second.

270
00:13:28.274 --> 00:13:29.572
Why. you got something to hide?

271
00:13:29.676 --> 00:13:31.577
Was that Terrence
who got shot? Why?

272
00:13:31.711 --> 00:13:32.872
He ran.

273
00:13:33.579 --> 00:13:34.672
Can I look in here?

274
00:13:35.214 --> 00:13:37.547
Yes or no? What's in here
that you don't want me to see?

275
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.346
It ain't even mine. Go
ahead and look. man.

276
00:13:42.455 --> 00:13:43.799
How well do you
know your roommate?

277
00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:46.486
We met. like. three months ago
on Craigslist. He's a quiet dude.

278
00:13:46.592 --> 00:13:49.255
Okay. Well. he's got pills
here. he's got a few joints.

279
00:13:49.362 --> 00:13:51.695
This gives me probable cause
to search this whole place.

280
00:13:51.798 --> 00:13:53.096
You get that. right? No.

281
00:13:53.232 --> 00:13:54.598
Are you covering for him?

282
00:13:54.701 --> 00:13:57.079
That makes you an accessory
to the rape of a 12-year-old girl.

283
00:13:57.103 --> 00:13:58.127
Were you in on that?

284
00:13:58.438 --> 00:14:00.407
No. No. Look wherever
you want. man.

285
00:14:02.241 --> 00:14:03.368
Where was he last night?

286
00:14:03.543 --> 00:14:05.512
I don't know. I was working.
You can ask my boss.

287
00:14:05.611 --> 00:14:07.079
Believe me. I will.

288
00:14:11.117 --> 00:14:12.517
Your roommate
cut his hair recently?

289
00:14:12.819 --> 00:14:14.412
No. man. He always had a fade.

290
00:14:20.493 --> 00:14:22.587
Petty-ante drug possession
doesn't help me. Carisi.

291
00:14:22.695 --> 00:14:24.163
No stolen credit cards?

292
00:14:24.597 --> 00:14:26.589
Yes. the warrant is on its way.

293
00:14:26.699 --> 00:14:28.827
Get CSU up there.
Look for blood.

294
00:14:28.935 --> 00:14:30.995
the vic's DNA.
everything. Let's go.

295
00:14:32.538 --> 00:14:33.538
Tucker.

296
00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:35.517
What. you sleep with a
radio under your pillow?

297
00:14:35.541 --> 00:14:36.541
I don't need one.

298
00:14:36.609 --> 00:14:37.853
Police shoot another
young black man.

299
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:39.243
word travels. Is that them?

300
00:14:39.445 --> 00:14:41.090
Yes. Everything's
being taken care of.

301
00:14:41.114 --> 00:14:42.776
All right. I understand
I have 48 hours

302
00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:44.482
to talk to IAB and
give their statements.

303
00:14:44.584 --> 00:14:46.829
But if they take all 48. your
precinct's gonna be on fire.

304
00:14:46.853 --> 00:14:47.853
I'll talk to them.

305
00:14:48.020 --> 00:14:49.020
Not without me you won't.

306
00:14:49.088 --> 00:14:52.183
Ms. Denzler. Detective's
Endowment moving quickly also. eh?

307
00:14:52.558 --> 00:14:54.117
If you're here.
Tucker. I'm here.

308
00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:55.904
Easy. guys. We're all
on the same team. right?

309
00:14:55.928 --> 00:14:57.362
We were told that
our son was here.

310
00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.456
Terrence Reynolds.
Mrs. Reynolds...

311
00:14:59.565 --> 00:15:01.193
We got a call saying
that he was shot?

312
00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:02.300
He was.

313
00:15:02.735 --> 00:15:03.862
He's in surgery now.

314
00:15:03.970 --> 00:15:04.994
What happened?

315
00:15:05.104 --> 00:15:06.144
We're still investigating.

316
00:15:06.239 --> 00:15:07.605
What we do know is that your son

317
00:15:07.707 --> 00:15:09.039
led the police on a foot chase.

318
00:15:09.542 --> 00:15:11.306
Wait. the police shot him?

319
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:13.555
Do you know anything about
your son's whereabouts last night?

320
00:15:13.579 --> 00:15:15.480
No. He doesn't live
with us. You shot him?

321
00:15:15.581 --> 00:15:17.607
Why would you shoot him?
Calm down. Calm down.

322
00:15:18.317 --> 00:15:19.444
Is that his doctor?

323
00:15:19.552 --> 00:15:20.611
That's one of them.

324
00:15:32.598 --> 00:15:33.896
I'm so sorry.

325
00:15:35.368 --> 00:15:36.368
No.

326
00:15:38.070 --> 00:15:39.663
No. not my son.

327
00:15:42.074 --> 00:15:43.372
No.

328
00:15:48.381 --> 00:15:49.381
No.

329
00:15:57.290 --> 00:15:59.122
I saw him on TV. That's the guy.

330
00:15:59.225 --> 00:16:00.602
Okay. well. hold
on. take your time.

331
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:02.037
We need to make
sure. So look at them all.

332
00:16:02.061 --> 00:16:04.997
No. no. it's him. His hair's a
little bit shorter. but it's him.

333
00:16:10.269 --> 00:16:11.269
Um...

334
00:16:12.605 --> 00:16:14.870
That one looks
a little like him.

335
00:16:15.041 --> 00:16:17.306
but he's young in
that photo. Is it old?

336
00:16:17.777 --> 00:16:19.040
Uh. no. it's current.

337
00:16:19.512 --> 00:16:20.512
I'm...

338
00:16:21.481 --> 00:16:24.679
I'm sorry. I think he was older
and tougher-looking than him.

339
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:26.651
Okay.

340
00:16:29.755 --> 00:16:31.121
Thank you so much for coming in.

341
00:16:31.357 --> 00:16:32.450
You get an ID?

342
00:16:32.558 --> 00:16:34.356
Not really. Rollins?

343
00:16:34.961 --> 00:16:37.260
Immediately. He picked
Terrence right out of the gate.

344
00:16:37.463 --> 00:16:38.487
It's 50-50.

345
00:16:38.598 --> 00:16:40.976
Three cops who thought he was
pulling a gun that we can't find.

346
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:43.745
Three cops we know that we've
worked with. I mean. Doom is rock-solid.

347
00:16:43.769 --> 00:16:47.262
Okay. Carisi. bring in last
week's vic. show her a photo array.

348
00:16:47.507 --> 00:16:50.705
Go over every video from the
shooting. Maybe he tosses the gun.

349
00:16:51.544 --> 00:16:53.055
And. Rollins. where
the hell is the DNA?

350
00:16:53.079 --> 00:16:54.239
It just went down to the lab.

351
00:16:54.280 --> 00:16:56.681
So follow it. Test it
yourself if you have to.

352
00:17:02.154 --> 00:17:03.713
Terrence Reynolds
fit the description

353
00:17:03.823 --> 00:17:05.416
of the rapist we were pursuing.

354
00:17:05.725 --> 00:17:07.057
Did you identify yourself?

355
00:17:07.159 --> 00:17:08.991
Yes. then the suspect fled.

356
00:17:09.462 --> 00:17:11.822
At what point did you find it
necessary to fire your weapon?

357
00:17:11.864 --> 00:17:13.662
When the suspect
took cover in a doorway

358
00:17:13.766 --> 00:17:15.598
and pulled something
out of his waistband.

359
00:17:15.768 --> 00:17:16.768
At that moment.

360
00:17:16.836 --> 00:17:20.705
I clearly felt that my life and the lives
of my fellow officers were in danger.

361
00:17:20.940 --> 00:17:22.067
Why did you feel that way?

362
00:17:22.475 --> 00:17:23.670
He fled without cause.

363
00:17:24.544 --> 00:17:27.708
We gave chase. and when
we subsequently cornered him.

364
00:17:27.813 --> 00:17:30.325
he reached for something that I
had reason to believe was a gun.

365
00:17:30.349 --> 00:17:31.349
Did you see it?

366
00:17:31.417 --> 00:17:33.215
We were told the
suspect was armed.

367
00:17:33.419 --> 00:17:36.548
I felt my life. and the lives of
my fellow officers. were in danger.

368
00:17:37.189 --> 00:17:38.384
So you emptied your clip?

369
00:17:38.691 --> 00:17:41.024
No. I fired three times.

370
00:17:41.127 --> 00:17:43.539
Your two fellow officers
emptied their clips.

371
00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:44.826
Why did you stop at three?

372
00:17:45.031 --> 00:17:46.031
Uh...

373
00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:48.730
I didn't have as good a
visual on him as they did.

374
00:17:48.834 --> 00:17:49.858
Oh. you didn't?

375
00:17:50.369 --> 00:17:52.463
And yet you knew he was
armed at the time you fired?

376
00:17:54.373 --> 00:17:57.832
I felt my life. and the lives of
my fellow officers. were in danger.

377
00:18:00.546 --> 00:18:01.546
Are we good?

378
00:18:02.114 --> 00:18:04.049
Almost. One more thing.

379
00:18:07.453 --> 00:18:08.453
Your story.

380
00:18:09.355 --> 00:18:10.983
besides the amount
of shots you fired.

381
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:13.889
is remarkably consistent
with that of your fellow officers.

382
00:18:14.427 --> 00:18:16.328
The truth is
consistent. Lieutenant.

383
00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:19.259
Maybe. But usually
it's not verbatim.

384
00:18:19.632 --> 00:18:20.872
Next time you prep your people.

385
00:18:20.900 --> 00:18:22.077
tell them to use
their own words.

386
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:23.381
I'll take that under advisement.

387
00:18:23.436 --> 00:18:24.563
Please do.

388
00:18:25.805 --> 00:18:27.034
I'll be right back.

389
00:18:36.749 --> 00:18:39.344
Showing up in person. Bad news?

390
00:18:39.585 --> 00:18:41.486
Didn't want to
put it in writing.

391
00:18:41.587 --> 00:18:42.680
Bad ID on the first vic?

392
00:18:42.822 --> 00:18:43.822
It's worse.

393
00:18:45.224 --> 00:18:46.522
The DNA came back.

394
00:18:47.560 --> 00:18:51.327
The two push-ins are a match.
but our perp. whoever he is.

395
00:18:52.298 --> 00:18:53.527
isn't Terrence Reynolds.

396
00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.596
So. our rapist
is still out there.

397
00:18:56.736 --> 00:18:59.171
and more to the point...

398
00:18:59.905 --> 00:19:01.737
These three officers
killed an innocent man.

399
00:19:14.987 --> 00:19:16.227
<i>How many more?</i>

400
00:19:17.390 --> 00:19:19.518
<i>How many more
times must we mourn</i>

401
00:19:19.692 --> 00:19:21.854
<i>the death of an
innocent black youth</i>

402
00:19:22.428 --> 00:19:25.023
<i>at the hands of those who
are sworn to serve and protect?</i>

403
00:19:25.131 --> 00:19:26.895
<i>How many more have to die?</i>

404
00:19:27.266 --> 00:19:32.432
<i>No more! No more!
No more! No more!</i>

405
00:19:32.972 --> 00:19:34.565
So. the whole city's on boil.

406
00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:37.507
I have to convene a grand jury.

407
00:19:38.611 --> 00:19:40.842
The DA says it's my last
chance to work my way back

408
00:19:40.980 --> 00:19:42.608
into the good
graces of City Hall.

409
00:19:42.715 --> 00:19:44.026
So they're hanging
you out to dry.

410
00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:45.290
Politicians want an indictment.

411
00:19:45.384 --> 00:19:47.744
the DA wants an indictment.
If I fail to get it. it's on me.

412
00:19:47.787 --> 00:19:49.449
So you'll push for
one. even though

413
00:19:49.555 --> 00:19:51.195
those officers were
just doing their jobs?

414
00:19:51.257 --> 00:19:52.520
Their jobs?

415
00:19:52.625 --> 00:19:55.185
They fired at an unarmed
college student 35 times.

416
00:19:55.294 --> 00:19:58.594
We were in hot pursuit
of a dangerous rapist.

417
00:19:58.864 --> 00:20:02.062
Terrence matched the BOLO
down to his jersey. He ran...

418
00:20:02.168 --> 00:20:03.693
A black man in a
basketball jersey

419
00:20:03.803 --> 00:20:05.533
runs when he gets
stopped by the police?

420
00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.015
You're right. he deserves
the death penalty.

421
00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:08.119
That's not what I'm saying.

422
00:20:08.174 --> 00:20:09.608
It's not?

423
00:20:11.844 --> 00:20:14.746
Counselor and Lieutenant Benson.

424
00:20:15.114 --> 00:20:18.016
I trust you're here to
assure our friend. Mr. Barba.

425
00:20:18.117 --> 00:20:20.109
that this was a good shooting?

426
00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:24.384
Or does this relate to the serial
rapist you haven't caught yet?

427
00:20:24.490 --> 00:20:25.490
Actually...

428
00:20:27.093 --> 00:20:28.584
Actually. I was just leaving.

429
00:20:33.833 --> 00:20:36.496
NYPD's PR czar
waltzes into my office.

430
00:20:36.602 --> 00:20:40.130
This must be my lucky day. What
does the Commissioner want now?

431
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:43.641
I know City Hall has their
agenda. but what we want.

432
00:20:43.809 --> 00:20:46.404
what this city
needs. is clarity.

433
00:20:46.512 --> 00:20:48.447
Clarity? These cops
were chasing down

434
00:20:48.547 --> 00:20:52.143
an armed suspect who
raped a 12-year-old.

435
00:20:52.785 --> 00:20:54.014
Get ahead of it.

436
00:20:54.687 --> 00:20:57.418
Explain why New York
isn't Baltimore or Ferguson.

437
00:20:57.523 --> 00:21:00.687
Or Cleveland or Los
Angeles or Staten Island.

438
00:21:02.661 --> 00:21:03.661
You see the problem?

439
00:21:03.763 --> 00:21:05.803
There's a pattern.
This wasn't a part of it.

440
00:21:06.966 --> 00:21:08.901
The sooner the grand
jury clears these three.

441
00:21:09.001 --> 00:21:10.867
the sooner the city
can begin to heal.

442
00:21:12.304 --> 00:21:14.967
It used to be a rush to
judgment. Now it's a rush to heal.

443
00:21:15.674 --> 00:21:18.166
Mr. Barba. Reverend Curtis
would like to speak with you.

444
00:21:18.577 --> 00:21:19.670
I'll call him back.

445
00:21:19.779 --> 00:21:21.042
Actually. he's here.

446
00:21:21.614 --> 00:21:22.877
Mr. Barba.

447
00:21:23.282 --> 00:21:24.282
Reverend Curtis.

448
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:26.284
Counselor Henderson.

449
00:21:26.385 --> 00:21:27.444
Deputy Commissioner.

450
00:21:27.553 --> 00:21:28.897
Glad to see you've
taken an interest.

451
00:21:28.921 --> 00:21:29.921
Always.

452
00:21:31.423 --> 00:21:34.086
Mr. and Mrs. Reynolds. on
behalf of the Police Commissioner.

453
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:38.328
I would like to express
our sincerest condolences.

454
00:21:39.865 --> 00:21:40.865
Thank you.

455
00:21:40.933 --> 00:21:42.561
I was just telling Mr. Barba.

456
00:21:43.235 --> 00:21:46.728
the Commissioner wants a
full and thorough investigation

457
00:21:46.839 --> 00:21:49.070
to ensure justice is served.

458
00:21:49.175 --> 00:21:51.576
I'm sure he does. As do we.

459
00:21:51.744 --> 00:21:53.440
Now. you're the
first to hear this.

460
00:21:54.079 --> 00:21:57.811
NYPD is suspending
the officers involved.

461
00:21:57.917 --> 00:21:58.917
Without pay?

462
00:21:59.185 --> 00:22:00.185
That's a union issue.

463
00:22:00.920 --> 00:22:04.618
I'll leave you in the very
capable hands of the ADA.

464
00:22:06.926 --> 00:22:08.485
Mr. and Mrs. Reynolds. Please.

465
00:22:10.162 --> 00:22:12.290
They've put you in
the hot seat. Mr. Barba.

466
00:22:12.398 --> 00:22:14.230
I just want to get to the truth.

467
00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:15.527
We all do.

468
00:22:15.634 --> 00:22:18.263
Unfortunately. recent grand
juries have been rigged.

469
00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:20.532
So our community has
lost faith in the process.

470
00:22:20.639 --> 00:22:22.017
This process is
going to be different.

471
00:22:22.041 --> 00:22:25.034
We're here to ensure that.
We're going to be proactive.

472
00:22:25.144 --> 00:22:26.421
Inciting the
public will not help.

473
00:22:26.445 --> 00:22:27.879
That's not our intention.

474
00:22:28.013 --> 00:22:29.743
The last thing we
want is more violence.

475
00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:32.341
We're going to conduct
a parallel investigation.

476
00:22:32.751 --> 00:22:34.276
An independent autopsy.

477
00:22:34.453 --> 00:22:35.819
We want to offer another avenue

478
00:22:35.921 --> 00:22:38.721
for people who might not feel
comfortable talking with law enforcement.

479
00:22:38.791 --> 00:22:40.020
Okay. I appreciate that.

480
00:22:40.125 --> 00:22:43.095
And I'd also appreciate any
evidence you find coming directly to me.

481
00:22:43.195 --> 00:22:44.754
Let's not play this
out in the press.

482
00:22:44.864 --> 00:22:47.390
My job is to advocate
for the family.

483
00:22:47.499 --> 00:22:49.991
I will do whatever is
in their best interest.

484
00:22:50.102 --> 00:22:53.470
And that interest.
for all of us. is justice.

485
00:22:55.608 --> 00:22:57.338
As it is for all of us.

486
00:22:58.210 --> 00:22:59.410
Thank you again for coming in.

487
00:22:59.545 --> 00:23:04.711
Again. Mr. and Mrs. Reynolds.
we are all very sorry for your loss.

488
00:23:06.318 --> 00:23:07.513
Thank you.

489
00:23:10.723 --> 00:23:13.750
I know you're tired of this
Kabuki. Rafael. and so am I.

490
00:23:14.894 --> 00:23:17.295
This year alone.
almost 700 people

491
00:23:17.396 --> 00:23:18.956
have been shot and
killed by the police.

492
00:23:18.998 --> 00:23:22.799
Now that won't stop until
cities start to send a message.

493
00:23:26.305 --> 00:23:28.900
I can't imagine the
pressure that you're under.

494
00:23:29.775 --> 00:23:32.472
Please do the right thing here.

495
00:23:46.492 --> 00:23:49.155
We find out about our suspension
by hearing it on the news?

496
00:23:49.828 --> 00:23:51.262
A lot of respect.

497
00:23:51.363 --> 00:23:55.459
Get used to it. City Hall's
looking for sacrificial lambs.

498
00:23:55.801 --> 00:23:56.801
Hey.

499
00:23:57.436 --> 00:23:59.337
Detective Rollins.
Sergeant Donlan.

500
00:23:59.772 --> 00:24:01.206
Detective. Hey.

501
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:02.666
What are you doing here?

502
00:24:05.010 --> 00:24:06.171
She came to meet me.

503
00:24:06.578 --> 00:24:07.578
Well.

504
00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:09.675
I was just leaving.

505
00:24:09.949 --> 00:24:12.441
Yeah. and I got my wife
and kids crying at home.

506
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:15.119
Your first?

507
00:24:15.587 --> 00:24:16.587
Yeah.

508
00:24:16.789 --> 00:24:17.916
Good luck.

509
00:24:20.726 --> 00:24:21.750
Thanks.

510
00:24:23.862 --> 00:24:24.862
Sorry about those guys.

511
00:24:24.964 --> 00:24:27.297
Yeah. it's all right. You
guys are under a lot of stress.

512
00:24:27.466 --> 00:24:29.833
Yeah. about that...

513
00:24:32.972 --> 00:24:35.567
You know Barba. Any idea
where he's going with this?

514
00:24:36.608 --> 00:24:37.837
Honestly. I don't.

515
00:24:41.647 --> 00:24:46.347
Your Lieutenant. Fin. and
Carisi. were all on the scene.

516
00:24:47.987 --> 00:24:49.546
SVU's got our back. right?

517
00:24:50.356 --> 00:24:51.824
We know you're good cops.

518
00:24:55.294 --> 00:24:56.592
He was cornered.

519
00:24:57.563 --> 00:24:59.088
his hand went to his waist.

520
00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:01.300
That's when you
use deadly force.

521
00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:04.129
He was guilty of something.
Why else would he run?

522
00:25:04.470 --> 00:25:08.532
Maybe it's best not to
talk about this in public.

523
00:25:10.943 --> 00:25:13.071
Come on. how about
I give you a lift home?

524
00:25:14.013 --> 00:25:15.208
You think I'm drunk?

525
00:25:15.614 --> 00:25:16.614
Mmm.

526
00:25:17.983 --> 00:25:18.983
I'm fine.

527
00:25:25.257 --> 00:25:26.725
What difference does it make?

528
00:25:28.660 --> 00:25:30.060
They're gonna
hang us. aren't they?

529
00:25:38.771 --> 00:25:41.002
Mr. Barba. you didn't
have to come down.

530
00:25:41.140 --> 00:25:43.700
Yeah. I did. I read your report.

531
00:25:45.044 --> 00:25:47.639
Look. I know this
is a tragic situation.

532
00:25:48.881 --> 00:25:51.043
but like it says.
they're not bad apples.

533
00:25:51.216 --> 00:25:54.880
No charges of excessive
force. No accusations of racism.

534
00:25:54.987 --> 00:25:57.821
Commendations for integrity.
meritorious police duty...

535
00:25:57.923 --> 00:25:59.801
So even our best and brightest
are gunning down innocents.

536
00:25:59.825 --> 00:26:01.384
They believed the
suspect had a weapon

537
00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:04.039
and was a threat to themselves
and civilians. It's all in our report.

538
00:26:04.063 --> 00:26:07.625
Yes. I know. I watched the deposition
as well. There appears to be a gap.

539
00:26:09.635 --> 00:26:12.195
You said. "One more
thing." Then it cut out.

540
00:26:14.973 --> 00:26:16.168
A glitch?

541
00:26:16.775 --> 00:26:21.804
No. We thought that they just
sounded a little over-coached.

542
00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:24.040
Over-coached. or coached to lie?

543
00:26:26.318 --> 00:26:27.547
The former.

544
00:26:28.187 --> 00:26:29.780
They each quoted. verbatim.

545
00:26:29.922 --> 00:26:32.016
the legal definition of the
necessary use of force.

546
00:26:32.157 --> 00:26:33.853
We hear that a lot. Lawyers.

547
00:26:34.793 --> 00:26:37.854
Bottom line. if I was in their
shoes. I'd have fired. too.

548
00:26:38.097 --> 00:26:39.531
Thirty-five times?

549
00:26:46.271 --> 00:26:47.603
Amanda... What?

550
00:26:48.907 --> 00:26:50.205
Declan. What are you doing here?

551
00:26:50.642 --> 00:26:52.235
How far along are you?

552
00:26:54.012 --> 00:26:57.312
I'm 4.000 miles away in Serbia trying
to take down a sex-trafficking ring.

553
00:26:57.416 --> 00:26:58.543
I still heard about it.

554
00:26:59.284 --> 00:27:00.445
Seven months.

555
00:27:01.753 --> 00:27:04.018
So that weekend back in
February. The blizzard...

556
00:27:04.957 --> 00:27:06.118
Yeah.

557
00:27:06.725 --> 00:27:07.725
It's mine?

558
00:27:10.195 --> 00:27:11.635
When were you
gonna tell me. darling?

559
00:27:11.663 --> 00:27:12.663
Well.

560
00:27:13.532 --> 00:27:16.001
like you just said. you
were 4.000 miles away.

561
00:27:16.101 --> 00:27:18.297
Didn't really know
how to get a hold of you.

562
00:27:18.670 --> 00:27:20.400
Fair enough. But I'm here now.

563
00:27:21.573 --> 00:27:22.734
For how long?

564
00:27:23.575 --> 00:27:24.575
Can't say.

565
00:27:25.544 --> 00:27:27.410
Which is why I didn't
bother you with it.

566
00:27:27.579 --> 00:27:29.445
You don't have
time to worry about it.

567
00:27:29.648 --> 00:27:30.775
I'm not worried.

568
00:27:30.949 --> 00:27:34.386
Okay. but it's gonna be okay.
My mom's coming up. Um...

569
00:27:37.189 --> 00:27:38.953
It's my decision.

570
00:27:39.691 --> 00:27:41.069
Don't worry. it's not
your responsibility.

571
00:27:41.093 --> 00:27:42.093
But it is.

572
00:27:42.961 --> 00:27:44.190
We gotta talk.

573
00:27:44.296 --> 00:27:46.231
I'm not just gonna walk
away. you know that.

574
00:27:46.331 --> 00:27:48.163
Okay. We'll talk.

575
00:27:49.334 --> 00:27:50.700
Right now I gotta get upstairs.

576
00:27:51.069 --> 00:27:52.069
It's gonna be fine.

577
00:27:52.171 --> 00:27:53.414
Right now there's a lot going on

578
00:27:53.438 --> 00:27:54.997
that I gotta deal
with. We'll talk.

579
00:27:56.475 --> 00:27:57.841
That's my phone.

580
00:27:59.378 --> 00:28:02.542
You call that number.
I'm on a plane in an hour.

581
00:28:18.297 --> 00:28:19.537
The grand jury starts tomorrow.

582
00:28:19.698 --> 00:28:23.100
My advice. make sure your
guys and your guys. especially.

583
00:28:23.202 --> 00:28:24.602
tell the truth in
their own words.

584
00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:26.247
If they sound coached.
or too legalistic...

585
00:28:26.271 --> 00:28:28.001
They'll do fine.
It's a tragedy...

586
00:28:28.106 --> 00:28:29.836
But it was a good shoot.

587
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:33.368
Tom Wolfe was right. Sooner
or later. all cops become Irish.

588
00:28:33.478 --> 00:28:35.709
Look. I don't get to
voir dire a grand jury.

589
00:28:35.814 --> 00:28:36.925
It's the first 23
through the door

590
00:28:36.949 --> 00:28:39.260
and everyone on that panel
will have heard about this case.

591
00:28:39.284 --> 00:28:41.150
Some of them will think
cops are never guilty.

592
00:28:41.253 --> 00:28:43.848
some will see this through the
prism of Ferguson or Baltimore.

593
00:28:43.956 --> 00:28:44.956
This is different.

594
00:28:45.057 --> 00:28:48.585
You think so. but all it
takes is 12 votes to indict.

595
00:28:49.428 --> 00:28:51.192
Mr. Barba... I said
no interruptions.

596
00:28:51.296 --> 00:28:52.730
I know. but...

597
00:28:54.666 --> 00:28:56.294
<i>Thank you for coming today.</i>

598
00:28:56.401 --> 00:28:58.529
<i>I'd like to warn you that
what you are about to see</i>

599
00:28:58.637 --> 00:29:00.469
<i>is as graphic as it is tragic.</i>

600
00:29:01.406 --> 00:29:03.375
<i>We've obtained
cell phone footage</i>

601
00:29:03.475 --> 00:29:06.570
<i>of Terrence Reynolds running
for his life from the police.</i>

602
00:29:07.145 --> 00:29:10.411
<i>A resident of the building across
the way took it from his window.</i>

603
00:29:11.850 --> 00:29:15.514
<i>Here we see Terrence desperately
trying to open a locked door.</i>

604
00:29:15.687 --> 00:29:16.998
<i>while reaching for his
keys.</i> CAMPESI: <i>Stop!</i>

605
00:29:17.022 --> 00:29:18.342
<i>Hands where I can see them.</i>

606
00:29:18.423 --> 00:29:19.968
<i>He attempts to put his hands up.</i>

607
00:29:19.992 --> 00:29:22.962
<i>turning towards the officer
to comply with his commands.</i>

608
00:29:23.595 --> 00:29:26.463
<i>The officers begin
firing their weapons.</i>

609
00:29:27.499 --> 00:29:31.027
<i>Here it is in slow
motion. Watch closely.</i>

610
00:29:32.504 --> 00:29:34.473
<i>He keeps trying
to put his hands up</i>

611
00:29:34.573 --> 00:29:36.508
<i>even after his
body hits the ground</i>

612
00:29:36.608 --> 00:29:39.134
<i>but the officers
just continue to fire.</i>

613
00:29:39.244 --> 00:29:43.579
<i>until the ninth and final
bullet pierces his body.</i>

614
00:29:49.321 --> 00:29:50.949
This changes things.

615
00:29:51.390 --> 00:29:52.949
It doesn't change a damn thing.

616
00:29:53.091 --> 00:29:54.369
It does. It's out there.

617
00:29:54.393 --> 00:29:55.986
Hold on.

618
00:29:58.163 --> 00:29:59.461
I know this looks bad.

619
00:30:00.065 --> 00:30:02.227
But this is not the
angle that they had.

620
00:30:02.868 --> 00:30:05.702
If it were. of course. they
would never have taken the shot.

621
00:30:07.205 --> 00:30:09.470
They were in the
heat of the chase.

622
00:30:09.574 --> 00:30:12.009
it was dark. they
were in the projects.

623
00:30:12.144 --> 00:30:13.344
They were following procedure.

624
00:30:13.378 --> 00:30:15.973
They were doing what any cop
would have done in their situation.

625
00:30:16.081 --> 00:30:17.174
Any cop?

626
00:30:17.883 --> 00:30:19.010
Even you?

627
00:30:24.956 --> 00:30:26.956
Anyone who's seen
the smoking guns video

628
00:30:26.992 --> 00:30:29.655
knows that Terrence
Reynolds was shot in cold blood

629
00:30:29.795 --> 00:30:31.039
for the crime of
running while black.

630
00:30:31.063 --> 00:30:33.141
What do you think the chances
are your clients will get indicted?

631
00:30:33.165 --> 00:30:37.500
These police officers put their
lives in danger to protect all of us.

632
00:30:37.602 --> 00:30:38.962
The only comment I have...

633
00:30:39.004 --> 00:30:42.099
Terrence's murderers will have
the right to counsel. the right to trial.

634
00:30:42.207 --> 00:30:43.698
Terrence was
deprived of those rights.

635
00:30:43.809 --> 00:30:45.937
In one instant.
these three officers

636
00:30:46.044 --> 00:30:48.673
were his judge.
jury. and executioner.

637
00:30:48.880 --> 00:30:52.009
The police believed the suspect
was armed and dangerous.

638
00:30:54.086 --> 00:30:58.387
When we arrived at the bodega we
secured a security still of the suspect.

639
00:30:58.490 --> 00:31:01.050
which closely matched
our sketch of the rapist.

640
00:31:02.027 --> 00:31:04.360
In this security photo.
as well as the sketch.

641
00:31:04.463 --> 00:31:06.022
the suspect clearly has an afro.

642
00:31:06.331 --> 00:31:08.232
Terrence Reynolds'
hair was short-cropped.

643
00:31:08.333 --> 00:31:09.995
With the cap it's hard to tell.

644
00:31:10.102 --> 00:31:12.799
But they both wore a
distinctive basketball jersey.

645
00:31:12.904 --> 00:31:15.032
Just to be clear.
Terrence Reynolds.

646
00:31:15.140 --> 00:31:17.132
the man who was
killed by police gunfire.

647
00:31:17.275 --> 00:31:20.268
was not the man at this ATM?

648
00:31:20.645 --> 00:31:21.738
No.

649
00:31:21.847 --> 00:31:23.907
But at the time we had
no way of knowing that.

650
00:31:24.015 --> 00:31:25.210
The 10-13 that came in

651
00:31:25.317 --> 00:31:27.462
said the suspect was running
towards the Clayton Powell houses.

652
00:31:27.486 --> 00:31:28.749
And what is a 10-13?

653
00:31:28.854 --> 00:31:30.686
Officer in need of assistance.

654
00:31:30.789 --> 00:31:34.089
Any cop hears that. he drops
what he's doing and responds.

655
00:31:34.192 --> 00:31:35.592
To your knowledge.
was any officer

656
00:31:35.694 --> 00:31:37.026
actually in danger
at that moment?

657
00:31:37.162 --> 00:31:38.442
They were on the
heels of someone

658
00:31:38.497 --> 00:31:40.377
they believed to be an
armed and violent rapist.

659
00:31:40.499 --> 00:31:42.968
So. yeah. that would
constitute danger.

660
00:31:43.101 --> 00:31:47.596
If the suspect was much
younger than the actual rapist.

661
00:31:47.706 --> 00:31:50.471
unarmed and innocent.
what would that constitute?

662
00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:53.273
Hindsight.

663
00:31:55.814 --> 00:31:58.249
Is that what you would
say to Mr. Reynolds' family?

664
00:31:59.217 --> 00:32:00.708
Terrence was a good son.

665
00:32:02.287 --> 00:32:06.418
He was working part-time
at an animal hospital

666
00:32:06.525 --> 00:32:08.357
while he was
going for his degree.

667
00:32:09.761 --> 00:32:13.357
Has your son ever been charged
with a crime. Mr. Reynolds?

668
00:32:14.199 --> 00:32:16.759
He'd been ticketed a few times.

669
00:32:16.868 --> 00:32:19.337
Once for running a
stop sign on his bicycle.

670
00:32:20.205 --> 00:32:22.697
Uh. once for possession of a joint.
- Nothing violent?

671
00:32:22.808 --> 00:32:24.674
No. Never.

672
00:32:25.911 --> 00:32:29.643
Why do you think he ran that
night. when the cops stopped him?

673
00:32:33.685 --> 00:32:38.180
In our neighborhood. relations
with the police are not good.

674
00:32:39.658 --> 00:32:42.822
Many of Terrence's friends
get arrested for no reason.

675
00:32:43.462 --> 00:32:46.261
They can't make bail.
they lose their jobs.

676
00:32:47.666 --> 00:32:51.398
My son didn't do anything wrong.

677
00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:55.252
But he knew that
wouldn't make a difference.

678
00:32:57.108 --> 00:32:59.043
He was just trying to go home.

679
00:33:02.981 --> 00:33:05.644
When the suspect
hid in the doorway.

680
00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:07.981
he moved his hand
towards his belt

681
00:33:08.086 --> 00:33:11.523
in a way that indicated he
might be reaching for a weapon.

682
00:33:12.791 --> 00:33:15.056
In no way is this
reckless endangerment.

683
00:33:15.894 --> 00:33:19.558
In no way is this criminally
negligent homicide.

684
00:33:19.731 --> 00:33:23.532
If it were me. I
would have believed

685
00:33:23.702 --> 00:33:25.830
that our lives and
the lives of bystanders

686
00:33:25.937 --> 00:33:27.166
were in danger.

687
00:33:27.939 --> 00:33:29.703
I would have done
what my officers did.

688
00:33:29.875 --> 00:33:31.605
Your officers made
the assumption

689
00:33:31.710 --> 00:33:34.009
that he was reaching for
a gun and not his keys?

690
00:33:35.447 --> 00:33:38.645
They're trained to assess
the situation by experience.

691
00:33:39.951 --> 00:33:43.149
In this case they were told
the suspect had a weapon.

692
00:33:43.288 --> 00:33:44.449
So. yes.

693
00:33:45.724 --> 00:33:48.091
Would the assumption
have been different

694
00:33:48.193 --> 00:33:53.393
if they'd been chasing a young
white woman or a man in a suit?

695
00:33:53.732 --> 00:33:55.564
Well. that's not
a fair comparison.

696
00:33:56.134 --> 00:33:58.194
The officers were in
pursuit of Mr. Reynolds

697
00:33:58.303 --> 00:34:02.206
because he matched the
description of a dangerous rapist.

698
00:34:02.307 --> 00:34:03.307
Lieutenant.

699
00:34:04.075 --> 00:34:06.510
how many rape suspects
have you chased in your career?

700
00:34:09.347 --> 00:34:11.839
I don't know. a hundred?

701
00:34:12.751 --> 00:34:16.483
And how many times have you
believed your life could be in danger?

702
00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:18.349
Would dozens be a fair estimate?

703
00:34:19.858 --> 00:34:20.985
Okay.

704
00:34:21.393 --> 00:34:24.852
According to your file.
you've shot two such suspects.

705
00:34:26.064 --> 00:34:27.225
Is that correct?

706
00:34:27.332 --> 00:34:28.459
Yes. that is correct.

707
00:34:28.600 --> 00:34:32.537
So you've had dozens of suspects
run. even pull weapons on you.

708
00:34:32.871 --> 00:34:35.238
yet time and again
you've chosen not to shoot.

709
00:34:35.974 --> 00:34:37.135
Terrence Reynolds was shot.

710
00:34:37.275 --> 00:34:38.868
Why? In my opinion.

711
00:34:40.011 --> 00:34:42.173
all police procedures
were followed.

712
00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:43.475
He was not facing them.

713
00:34:44.649 --> 00:34:46.675
Could they have waited
and called for backup?

714
00:34:49.421 --> 00:34:51.966
They were also wearing vests. Could
they have waited even half a second?

715
00:34:51.990 --> 00:34:52.990
Waited for what?

716
00:34:54.159 --> 00:34:55.821
For their partner to get shot?

717
00:34:56.494 --> 00:34:58.019
For their own head
to get blown off?

718
00:34:59.531 --> 00:35:01.090
They followed procedure.

719
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:05.502
I cannot speak to what I
would have done in that situation

720
00:35:05.604 --> 00:35:07.197
because I was not
in the line of fire.

721
00:35:07.305 --> 00:35:08.933
Neither were
any of the officers.

722
00:35:09.574 --> 00:35:11.099
I'll ask again.

723
00:35:12.110 --> 00:35:14.272
can you think of any
option these officers had

724
00:35:14.379 --> 00:35:15.972
besides shooting
Terrence Reynolds?

725
00:35:16.081 --> 00:35:17.208
In my opinion.

726
00:35:18.316 --> 00:35:20.808
all police procedures
were followed.

727
00:35:26.925 --> 00:35:29.236
The victims of the rapist you
believed you were pursuing

728
00:35:29.260 --> 00:35:30.820
were family members
of a police officer.

729
00:35:30.929 --> 00:35:32.807
Could that have influenced
your decision to shoot?

730
00:35:32.831 --> 00:35:36.199
We were told he had a gun on
the right side of his waistband.

731
00:35:37.235 --> 00:35:40.467
I shot because I thought the
suspect was reaching for that gun.

732
00:35:40.639 --> 00:35:42.107
But you didn't see a gun?

733
00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:44.104
I saw him reach
for his waistband.

734
00:35:44.209 --> 00:35:46.804
He was turning
toward Officer Dumas.

735
00:35:47.912 --> 00:35:50.404
I was in fear for
his life and mine.

736
00:35:50.548 --> 00:35:52.574
That's when instinct took over.

737
00:35:53.151 --> 00:35:55.552
You fired 16 times.
emptying your magazine.

738
00:35:55.654 --> 00:35:57.782
even after Terrence
Reynolds was on the ground.

739
00:35:58.490 --> 00:35:59.490
Why?

740
00:35:59.557 --> 00:36:01.526
We are trained to
shoot until we perceive

741
00:36:01.626 --> 00:36:03.288
that there is no
longer a threat.

742
00:36:05.063 --> 00:36:07.794
In the chaos. with
bullets ricocheting.

743
00:36:07.899 --> 00:36:10.232
you fire until the
shooting stops.

744
00:36:10.435 --> 00:36:12.995
So you. Detective Campesi
and Sergeant Donlan

745
00:36:13.104 --> 00:36:15.335
all thought the suspect
was reaching for a gun.

746
00:36:15.440 --> 00:36:17.841
You all thought your
lives were in danger.

747
00:36:18.643 --> 00:36:19.667
Yes.

748
00:36:20.078 --> 00:36:24.539
The only difference being. Detective
Dumas. you fired just three shots.

749
00:36:27.552 --> 00:36:28.552
Why is that?

750
00:36:35.093 --> 00:36:37.585
As I said. the
situation was chaotic.

751
00:36:38.730 --> 00:36:41.666
But I and my fellow
officers followed procedure.

752
00:36:43.601 --> 00:36:47.436
Just to clarify for the jury. I'd like to
show a video taken by a bystander.

753
00:36:49.607 --> 00:36:50.700
<i>Stop!</i>

754
00:36:51.576 --> 00:36:52.896
<i>Hands where I can see them.</i>

755
00:37:03.354 --> 00:37:04.794
Do you recall this
moment. Detective?

756
00:37:05.190 --> 00:37:07.159
Yes. RAFAEL: Your fellow
officers continued firing

757
00:37:07.258 --> 00:37:08.749
after the suspect was down?

758
00:37:09.327 --> 00:37:11.296
We still didn't see his hands.

759
00:37:11.396 --> 00:37:13.490
We still had reason to
believe that he was armed.

760
00:37:13.598 --> 00:37:15.032
So why did you stop firing?

761
00:37:16.534 --> 00:37:19.003
Again. I didn't have the
angle that you have here now.

762
00:37:19.104 --> 00:37:20.936
Could it have been
that you perceived

763
00:37:21.039 --> 00:37:22.439
that the threat had
been eliminated?

764
00:37:26.845 --> 00:37:28.177
I guess. You guess?

765
00:37:29.581 --> 00:37:31.421
Is it possible you
had second thoughts?

766
00:37:32.417 --> 00:37:34.061
Did you think you should
have waited to determine

767
00:37:34.085 --> 00:37:36.919
whether Terrence Reynolds
was. in fact. armed?

768
00:37:37.021 --> 00:37:38.819
Was. in fact. an actual threat?

769
00:37:38.957 --> 00:37:40.197
I don't know. He was turning...

770
00:37:40.225 --> 00:37:41.602
He was turning but
you didn't see a gun

771
00:37:41.626 --> 00:37:43.254
and that's why
you stopped firing.

772
00:37:43.995 --> 00:37:45.486
Isn't it. Detective?

773
00:37:47.165 --> 00:37:48.165
I don't know...

774
00:37:48.233 --> 00:37:51.795
If you and your fellow officers
had waited half a second longer.

775
00:37:51.903 --> 00:37:55.203
Terrence Reynolds
would be alive today.

776
00:37:56.775 --> 00:37:58.243
Would you agree with that?

777
00:38:09.954 --> 00:38:11.013
Yes.

778
00:38:28.540 --> 00:38:30.441
Hey. How'd it go up there?

779
00:38:30.542 --> 00:38:32.340
I can't talk about it
and neither can you.

780
00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:33.754
But Barba knows
what he's doing. right?

781
00:38:33.778 --> 00:38:34.871
Yeah. he does.

782
00:38:40.185 --> 00:38:41.312
She's in a mood.

783
00:38:41.452 --> 00:38:43.080
Yeah. Well. we all are.

784
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:51.272
You have in front of you the
charges of reckless endangerment

785
00:38:51.296 --> 00:38:54.357
in the first degree or
criminally negligent homicide.

786
00:38:54.465 --> 00:38:57.196
Before we vote.
is it possible for us

787
00:38:57.302 --> 00:38:58.930
to indict on more
serious charges?

788
00:39:00.004 --> 00:39:01.004
Excuse me?

789
00:39:01.639 --> 00:39:04.074
I don't think we're looking at
recklessness or negligence.

790
00:39:04.209 --> 00:39:06.178
I think we're looking
at murder here.

791
00:39:07.011 --> 00:39:09.207
Can we bring a charge like that?

792
00:39:11.349 --> 00:39:14.217
That is within your purview.

793
00:39:15.153 --> 00:39:18.885
but I would like the
grand jury to understand

794
00:39:18.990 --> 00:39:21.789
that in order to prove
manslaughter one or above.

795
00:39:21.893 --> 00:39:24.192
you have to prove intent.

796
00:39:24.495 --> 00:39:27.294
That's a much
higher legal standard

797
00:39:27.465 --> 00:39:30.264
requiring an increased
level of mens rea.

798
00:39:30.401 --> 00:39:33.132
intent versus negligence.

799
00:39:34.005 --> 00:39:36.406
Well. I'd like you to
explain that standard.

800
00:39:36.507 --> 00:39:38.533
For manslaughter.
murder. whatever.

801
00:39:38.710 --> 00:39:40.736
You know. walk us
through everything.

802
00:39:43.081 --> 00:39:46.279
I can. But before I do. I'd
like to see a show of hands.

803
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:49.218
How many of you would like to
hear a definition of those charges?

804
00:40:00.865 --> 00:40:04.427
<i>We are extremely gratified
that the grand jury has decided</i>

805
00:40:04.535 --> 00:40:07.630
<i>to indict Sergeant Donlan
and Detective Campesi</i>

806
00:40:07.739 --> 00:40:11.676
<i>on manslaughter one. and Detective
Dumas on reckless endangerment.</i>

807
00:40:11.809 --> 00:40:14.802
<i>This is just the first step
toward justice for Terrence.</i>

808
00:40:14.913 --> 00:40:16.745
<i>We will continue to
do everything we can</i>

809
00:40:16.848 --> 00:40:19.682
<i>to make sure these
officers are held accountable.</i>

810
00:40:19.784 --> 00:40:21.462
<i>Would the parents like
to make a statement?</i>

811
00:40:21.486 --> 00:40:24.149
<i>Obviously. we are
pleased with the indictment.</i>

812
00:40:24.322 --> 00:40:26.791
<i>This is just the
beginning of a long trial...</i>

813
00:40:26.891 --> 00:40:28.792
Well. the DA did
what City Hall wanted.

814
00:40:28.893 --> 00:40:31.089
Blame the cops. keep the peace.

815
00:40:31.229 --> 00:40:33.425
It's just an indictment.
It's not going anywhere.

816
00:40:33.531 --> 00:40:36.763
Son of a bitch. Barba. Good
luck next time he needs a cop.

817
00:40:36.868 --> 00:40:39.531
This might not all be on
Barba. Upping the charges?

818
00:40:39.671 --> 00:40:41.537
Sounds to me like he
had a runaway grand jury.

819
00:40:41.739 --> 00:40:44.903
Runaway. my ass. Barba
led and they followed.

820
00:40:45.009 --> 00:40:46.204
Hey. well. the good thing is.

821
00:40:46.311 --> 00:40:48.791
if this does go to trial. there's
no way they can prove intent.

822
00:40:48.846 --> 00:40:51.286
After what happened today.
you're gonna trust a New York jury?

823
00:40:51.349 --> 00:40:52.817
And what are you
worried about. Doom?

824
00:40:55.520 --> 00:40:56.749
Excuse me?

825
00:40:57.388 --> 00:40:58.832
You want to tell me
what you said up there

826
00:40:58.856 --> 00:41:00.484
that you only got
reckless endangerment?

827
00:41:00.591 --> 00:41:01.591
Wait. easy...

828
00:41:01.693 --> 00:41:03.570
And I want to know what your
lieutenant said up there. too.

829
00:41:03.594 --> 00:41:04.872
That's enough. Okay. okay. okay.

830
00:41:04.896 --> 00:41:07.730
Guys. this is not the time.

831
00:41:23.147 --> 00:41:25.116
Hey. What's his status?

832
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:27.577
He didn't make it.

833
00:41:27.685 --> 00:41:29.730
I mean. he's shot in the face
they couldn't do anything for him.

834
00:41:29.754 --> 00:41:32.622
Traffic stop gone bad.
They got the shooter.

835
00:41:34.592 --> 00:41:35.719
That the wife?

836
00:41:36.127 --> 00:41:37.254
Yeah.

837
00:41:37.562 --> 00:41:39.087
Two kids. 24.

838
00:41:40.598 --> 00:41:41.930
A rookie.

839
00:41:43.134 --> 00:41:45.501
- Does it get any worse?
- It might.

840
00:41:46.637 --> 00:41:48.435
The Mayor's on his way up.
